{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it illegal to smoke on hospital grounds",
        "additional_details": "We are concerned about smoking at hospitals, and believe the smoke free signage used by many hospitals is not effective.\r\n \r\nSmoking poses a risk to patients and visitors attending the site, and smoke inhalation should not be a concern when attending an appointment at a hospital, especially when this is already meant to be a \u2018smokefree site\u2019.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to implement a law to make it illegal to smoke on hospital grounds, with fines for offenders. We believe signs are not working and staff do not possess the confidence to challenge patients/visitors smoking currently.",
